🏠💰 Save on Taxes! 🎯 Section 54F & Capital Gains Account Scheme Explained! 📚🧐

🤔Looking to save on capital gains tax? 💸📈 Discover the power of Section 54F! 🤝🏡 Invest your net sales amount from any property (except residential) in a new residential house to claim exemption. 🏘️✨ Remember, the new property must be purchased within 1 year before or 2 years after the sale or constructed within 3 years. Also, you should own just one residential house on the sale date (except the one you’re buying). 💯📅 And guess what? The Budget 2023 update brings a whopping Rs 10 crore deduction, effective from April 2023! 🎉💼

Introducing the Capital Gains Account Scheme (CGAS) 🏦💼 for tax-saving flexibility! 💪🌈 If you can’t reinvest your gains before the tax return deadline, deposit them into CGAS with any scheduled bank. 🏦💰 Your gains remain exempt just like reinvestment! 🌟🔄 Choose between Type A - Savings deposit for liquidity and Type B - Term deposit for higher interest. The RBI fixes the interest rate, and you can even withdraw from Type A, while Type B allows premature withdrawal with a process. 💼💳 So, no more worries about missing deadlines, use CGAS to plan your investments! 🗓️🚀 #TaxSavingTips #Section54F #CGAS #CapitalGainsAccountScheme #InvestWisely

👉 Disclaimer: Always consult a tax advisor for personalized advice. This post is for informational purposes only. #TaxExemption #FinancialFreedom #SmartInvesting 📊💼🏠

💝“Pink Tax” refers to the practice of charging higher prices for products and services marketed specifically to women, even when these products are similar or identical to those marketed to men. This gender-based pricing disparity can result in women paying more for items like clothing, personal care products, and services, leading to economic inequality.

❌To avoid the effects of the Pink Tax, women and females can consider the following strategies:
* 	Compare Prices: Compare the prices of similar products marketed to different genders. Sometimes, the price difference isn’t justified by any significant quality or functionality discrepancy.
* 	Choose Gender-Neutral Products: Opt for gender-neutral or unisex products when possible. These often come with lower price tags and are just as effective.
* 	Buy in Bulk: Buying essential products like toiletries in bulk can help save money in the long run, as unit prices tend to be lower.
* 	Look for Sales and Discounts: Keep an eye out for sales, discounts, and promotions on products you regularly use. This can help you save on items that are typically more expensive due to the Pink Tax.
* 	Support Brands That Address the Issue: Some brands actively work to eliminate gender-based pricing disparities. Supporting these brands can help promote change in the industry.

“💰 Unlock Extra Savings with Your Financial Moves! 💸

In the world of loans, there are usually two main players: Car 🚗 and Housing 🏠. But here’s a game-changer: when you’re ready to pre-pay any part or the entire loan amount, go after that Floating Rate of Interest first! 🏦

Why, you ask? Well, it’s simple. When you pre-pay these loans, you won’t face any pesky pre-payment penalties, and the banks will be left empty-handed! 🙌

But beware! If you mistakenly pre-pay a Fixed Rate of Interest loan, you might get hit with a penalty from the banks. 🚫

And if you’re dealing with both loans under Floating Rate of Interest, prioritize the one with the higher interest rate for extra savings! 📈

✅Stay ahead in the financial game with @financewithsanjay . 📊 Bow down to the wisdom of money! 🙏 #FinancialSavvy #MoneyMatters”

🇮🇳Premature withdrawal to be allowed on all bank FDs of up to Rs 1 crore: RBI hikes limit of non-callable FDs
.
🤔The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) on October 26, 2023, has increased the minimum amount for offering non-callable term deposits to Rs 1 crore from the existing Rs 15 lakh for banks. So, all customers will get an option to prematurely withdraw money from fixed deposits (FDs) of up to Rs 1 crore.

🇮🇳Non-callable fixed deposits refer to a category of term deposits that offer no premature withdrawal option before the completion of tenure. Once you invest in these deposits, your money will be locked for the entire tenure. You can only access the money once your FD matures.

📈In a notification released on October 26, 2023, the central bank said, “In terms of these instructions, banks have been permitted to offer domestic term deposits (TDs) without premature withdrawal option, provided that all TDs accepted from individuals for an amount of Rupees fifteen lakh and below shall have premature withdrawal-facility. Further, the banks have also been permitted to offer differential rate on interest on TDs based on non-callability of deposits (i.e., non-availability of premature withdrawal option) in addition to tenor and size of deposits.”
.

✅The Reserve Bank of India raised the Unified Payments Interface (UPI) payment limits for hospitals and educational institutions from ₹1 lakh to ₹5 lakh per transaction. The announcement was made by Governor Shaktikanta Das while unveiling the December bi-monthly monetary policy.

“The enhanced limit will help consumers make UPI payments of higher amounts for education and healthcare purposes,”

✅E-MANDATE
The cap on e-mandates for recurring online transactions was also hiked to ₹1 lakh.

Under the e-mandate framework, an additional factor of authentication (AFA) is required for recurring transactions exceeding ₹15,000 currently. This is now being raised to ₹1 lakh for mutual fund investments, insurance premia payments and credit card payments.

Want to get Car in 2024, at a Bumper Discount⁉️👇🏻

1. **Festive Season Offers:** Many dealerships in India offer attractive discounts and special deals during festive seasons. Purchasing a car during these times can often result in significant savings.

2. **End-of-Year Clearance Sales:** Dealerships may offer discounts on older models to clear their inventory at the end of the year, making it a good time to negotiate a lower price.

3. **Corporate Discounts:** Some car manufacturers provide special discounts for employees of certain companies. Check if your employer has any tie-ups with car manufacturers to avail exclusive discounts.

4. **Exchange Offers:** Explore exchange programs where you can trade in your old vehicle for a new one. Dealerships often provide additional discounts or benefits as part of these exchange deals.

5. **Government Schemes and Subsidies:** Keep an eye on any government schemes or subsidies related to car purchases. Depending on the region, there might be programs that offer financial incentives or tax benefits for buying specific types of vehicles.

🚗🚘Buying a Second Hand Car?👇🏻

1) Check Service Chart/Record, which shows Real number of Kilometres it has ran.

2) Service Record will also show maintenance Records.

3) Many Brokers sell car applying Doctor’s Tag 🏷️, so that buyers may think, it would have been driven carefully but who knows it’s fake, do check it out.👨‍⚕️🏥

4) After Buying 🚗, Transfer RC on your name, otherwise you’ll be in Big legal problem🙏

5) Get or Transfer Insurance under your name, again to avoid legalities and to claim Insurance easily📄
